[344.465395, "o", "\u001b[1;1HBASH(1)              General Commands Manual             BASH(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H       bash - GNU Bourne-Again SHell\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H       \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m [options] [command_string | file]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[1mCOPYRIGHT\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H       Bash  is  Copyright  (C)  1989-2022  by the Free Software\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H       Foundation, Inc.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H       \u001b[1mBash\u001b[0m is an  \u001b[1msh\u001b[0m-compatible  command  language  interpreter\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[1;1HBASH(1)              General Commands Manual             BASH(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H       bash - GNU Bourne-Again SHell\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H       \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m [options] [command_string | file]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[1mCOPYRIGHT\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H       Bash  is  Copyright  (C)  1989-2022  by the Free Software\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H       Foundation, Inc.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H       \u001b[1mBash\u001b"]
[344.465457, "o", "[0m is an  \u001b[1msh\u001b[0m-comp"]
[344.466401, "o", "atible  command  language  interpreter\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H...skipping...\r\n              expansion, \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution, process substitu‐\u001b[m\r\n              tion  and quote removal.  Each \u001b[4mpattern\u001b[24m examined is\u001b[m\r\n              expanded  using  tilde  expansion,  parameter  and\u001b[m\r\n              variable  expansion, arithmetic expansion, command\u001b[m\r\n              substitution, process substitution, and quote  re‐\u001b[m\r\n              moval.   If  the  \u001b[1mnocasematch\u001b[0m  shell option is en‐\u001b[m\r\n              abled, the match is performed  without  regard  to\u001b[m\r\n              the  case  of alphabetic characters.  When a match\u001b[m\r\n              is found, the corresponding \u001b[4mlist\u001b[24m is executed.   If\u001b[m\r\n              the \u001b[1m;;\u001b[0m operator is used, no subsequent matches are\u001b[m\r\n              attempted after the first pattern match.  Using \u001b[1m;&\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              in  place  of \u001b[1m;;\u001b[0m causes execution to continue with\u001b[m\r\n              the \u001b[4mlist\u001b[24m associated with the next set of p"]
[344.466484, "o", "atterns.\u001b[m\r\n "]
[344.467833, "o", "             Using  \u001b[1m;;&\u001b[0m in place of \u001b[1m;;\u001b[0m causes the shell to test\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7mal page bash(1) line 571/8010 7% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[345.373072, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[345.373652, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       and  variable expansion, \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution, arithmetic\u001b[m\r\n       expansion, and quote removal (see \u001b[1mEXPANSION\u001b[0m  below).   If\u001b[m\r\n       the variable has its \u001b[1minteger\u001b[0m attribute set, then \u001b[4mvalue\u001b[24m is\u001b[m\r\n       evaluated  as  an  arithmetic  expression  even  if   the\u001b[m\r\n       $((...))  expansion is not used (see \u001b[1mArithmetic\u001b[0m \u001b[1mExpansion\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       below).  Word splitting and pathname  expansion  are  not\u001b[m\r\n       performed.   Assignment statements may also appear as ar‐\u001b[m\r\n       guments to the \u001b[1malias\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mdeclare\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mtypeset\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mexport\u001b[0m, \u001b[1mreadonly\u001b[0m,\u001b[m\r\n       and  \u001b[1mlocal\u001b[0m builtin commands (\u001b[4mdeclaration\u001b[24m commands).  When\u001b[m\r\n       in \u001b[4mposix\u001b[24m \u001b[4mmode\u001b[24m, these builtins may appear in a command af‐\u001b[m\r\n       ter  one or more instances of the \u001b[1mcommand\u001b[0m builtin and re‐\u001b[m\r\n       tain these assignment statement properties.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       In the context where an assignment statemen"]
[345.373667, "o", "t is assigning\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7ml page bash(1) line 839/8010 11% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[345.920716, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[345.921659, "o", "...skipping...\r\n              jected  to  parameter expansion, \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitu‐\u001b[m\r\n              tion, and arithmetic expansion before being inter‐\u001b[m\r\n              preted  as a filename.  \u001b[1mPATH\u001b[0m is not used to search\u001b[m\r\n              for the resultant filename.\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mBASH_XTRACEFD\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              If set to an integer corresponding to a valid file\u001b[m\r\n              descriptor,  \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m will write the trace output gen‐\u001b[m\r\n              erated when \u001b[4mset\u001b[24m \u001b[4m-x\u001b[24m is enabled  to  that  file  de‐\u001b[m\r\n              scriptor.   The  file  descriptor  is  closed when\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mBASH_XTRACEFD\u001b[0m is unset or assigned  a  new  value.\u001b[m\r\n              Unsetting  \u001b[1mBASH_XTRACEFD\u001b[0m or assigning it the empty\u001b[m\r\n              string causes the trace output to be sent  to  the\u001b[m\r\n              standard  error.   Note that setting \u001b[1mBASH_XTRACEFD\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              to 2 (the standard error file descriptor) and then\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 137"]
[345.921678, "o", "0/8010 18% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[346.331905, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[346.332897, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[4mter\u001b[24m \u001b[4mand\u001b[24m \u001b[4mvariable\u001b[24m \u001b[4mexpansion\u001b[24m, \u001b[4m\u001b[7mcommand\u001b[27m\u001b[24m\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\u001b[4m\u001b[7msubs\u001b[27m\u001b[24m\u001b[4mtitution\u001b[24m,  \u001b[4marith‐\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mmetic\u001b[24m \u001b[4mexpansion\u001b[24m, \u001b[4mword\u001b[24m \u001b[4msplitting\u001b[24m, and \u001b[4mpathname\u001b[24m \u001b[4mexpansion\u001b[24m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       The order of expansions is: brace expansion; tilde expan‐\u001b[m\r\n       sion, parameter and variable expansion, arithmetic expan‐\u001b[m\r\n       sion,  and  \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution (done in a left-to-right\u001b[m\r\n       fashion); word splitting; and pathname expansion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       On systems that can support it, there  is  an  additional\u001b[m\r\n       expansion  available: \u001b[4mprocess\u001b[24m \u001b[4msubstitution\u001b[24m.  This is per‐\u001b[m\r\n       formed at the same time as  tilde,  parameter,  variable,\u001b[m\r\n       and arithmetic expansion and \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       After  these  expansions  are performed, quote characters\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 1902/8010 25% (press h for hel"]
[346.332951, "o", "p or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[346.708198, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[346.708231, "o", "       present in the original word are removed unless they have\u001b[m\r\n       been quoted themselves (\u001b[4mquote\u001b[24m \u001b[4mremoval\u001b[24m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Only brace expansion, word splitting, and pathname expan‐\u001b[m\r\n       sion can increase the number of words of  the  expansion;\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 1907/8010 25% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[347.060375, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[347.060497, "o", "       other  expansions  expand a single word to a single word.\u001b[m\r\n       The only exceptions to this are the  expansions  of  \"\u001b[1m$@\u001b[0m\"\u001b[m\r\n       and  \"\u001b[1m${\u001b[0m\u001b[4mname\u001b[24m\u001b[1m[@]}\u001b[0m\",  and, in most cases, \u001b[1m$*\u001b[0m and \u001b[1m${\u001b[0m\u001b[4mname\u001b[24m\u001b[1m[*]}\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       as explained above (see \u001b[1mPARAMETERS\u001b[0m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mBrace\u001b[0m \u001b[1mExpansion\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 1913/8010 25% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[347.398437, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[347.398814, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution, or parameter expansion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       ${\u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m}\u001b[m\r\n              The value of \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is substituted.  The braces\u001b[m\r\n              are required when \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is a positional param‐\u001b[m\r\n              eter with more than one digit, or  when  \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n              is  followed by a character which is not to be in‐\u001b[m\r\n              terpreted as part of its name.  The \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is a\u001b[m\r\n              shell  parameter as described above \u001b[1mPARAMETERS\u001b[0m) or\u001b[m\r\n              an array reference (\u001b[1mArrays\u001b[0m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       If the first character of  \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m  is  an  exclamation\u001b[m\r\n       point  (\u001b[1m!\u001b[0m), and \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is not a \u001b[4mnameref\u001b[24m, it introduces\u001b[m\r\n       a level of indirection.  \u001b[1mBash\u001b[0m uses the  value  formed  by\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2051/8010 26% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[348.088865, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[348.088921, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution, and arithmetic expansion.   If  \u001b[4mpa‐\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mrameter\u001b[24m is a nameref, this expands to the name of the pa‐\u001b[m\r\n       rameter referenced by \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m instead of performing the\u001b[m\r\n       complete  indirect expansion.  The exceptions to this are\u001b[m\r\n       the expansions of ${\u001b[1m!\u001b[0m\u001b[4mprefix\u001b[24m\u001b[1m*\u001b[0m} and  ${\u001b[1m!\u001b[0m\u001b[4mname\u001b[24m[\u001b[4m@\u001b[24m]}  described\u001b[m\r\n       below.  The exclamation point must immediately follow the\u001b[m\r\n       left brace in order to introduce indirection.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       In each of the cases below, \u001b[4mword\u001b[24m is subject to tilde  ex‐\u001b[m\r\n       pansion,  parameter  expansion, \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution, and\u001b[m\r\n       arithmetic expansion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       When not performing substring expansion, using the  forms\u001b[m\r\n       documented  below  (e.g., \u001b[1m:-\u001b[0m), \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m tests for a parameter\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2070/8010 27% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[348.605375, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[348.605402, "o", "       that is unset or null.  Omitting the colon results  in  a\u001b[m\r\n       test only for a parameter that is unset.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       ${\u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m\u001b[1m:-\u001b[0m\u001b[4mword\u001b[24m}\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mUse\u001b[0m  \u001b[1mDefault\u001b[0m  \u001b[1mValues\u001b[0m.   If  \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m  is unset or\u001b[m\r\n              null, the expansion of \u001b[4mword\u001b[24m is substituted.   Oth‐\u001b[m\r\n              erwise, the value of \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is substituted.\u001b[m\r\n       ${\u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m\u001b[1m:=\u001b[0m\u001b[4mword\u001b[24m}\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mAssign\u001b[0m  \u001b[1mDefault\u001b[0m  \u001b[1mValues\u001b[0m.  If \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is unset or\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2079/8010 27% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[349.040336, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[349.040987, "o", "...skipping...\r\n   \u001b[1m\u001b[7mCommand\u001b[27m\u001b[0m\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[7mSubs\u001b[27m\u001b[0m\u001b[1mtitution\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4m\u001b[7mCommand\u001b[27m\u001b[24m\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\u001b[4m\u001b[7msubs\u001b[27m\u001b[24m\u001b[4mtitution\u001b[24m allows the output of  a  command  to\u001b[m\r\n       replace the command name.  There are two forms:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m$(\u001b[0m\u001b[4mcommand\u001b[24m\u001b[1m)\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       or\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1m`\u001b[0m\u001b[4mcommand\u001b[24m\u001b[1m`\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mBash\u001b[0m  performs  the  expansion  by executing \u001b[4mcommand\u001b[24m in a\u001b[m\r\n       subshell environment and replacing the command  substitu‐\u001b[m\r\n       tion  with  the  standard output of the command, with any\u001b[m\r\n       trailing newlines deleted.   Embedded  newlines  are  not\u001b[m\r\n       deleted,  but  they may be removed during word splitting.\u001b[m\r\n       The \u001b[7mcommand subs\u001b[27mtitution \u001b[1m$(cat\u001b[0m \u001b[4mfile\u001b[24m\u001b[1m)\u001b[0m can be  replaced  by\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2371/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[351.802782, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K"]
[351.802979, "o", "\u001b[H\u001bM\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2370/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[351.858351, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K\u001b[H\u001bM              low.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2369/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[393.412605, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K\u001b[H\u001bM              splitting  and pathname expansion as described be‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2368/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[393.913785, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K\u001b[H\u001bM              The result of the expansion  is  subject  to  word\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2367/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[393.944378, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K\u001b[H\u001bM\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2366/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[393.975792, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K\u001b[H\u001bM              turn, and the expansion is the resultant list.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2365/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[394.006804, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K"]
[394.006832, "o", "\u001b[H\u001bM              tion  is  applied  to  each member of the array in\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2364/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[394.038933, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K\u001b[H\u001bM              array variable subscripted with \u001b[1m@\u001b[0m or \u001b[1m*\u001b[0m, the opera‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2363/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[394.070244, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KA\bA\r\u001b[K\u001b[H\u001bM              pansion is the resultant list.  If \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is an\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\r\u001b[K\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 2362/8010 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
